│ Understanding the Issue:\n\nThe issue occurs when InstCombine transforms a  │
│ select instruction with a samesign icmp in the true value and a false       │
│ constant in the false value. The transformation replaces the select with    │
│ just the true value (the samesign icmp), which is incorrect because it      │
│ changes the poison behavior.\n\nIn the source code:\n- When x = 0, cmp2     │
│ (icmp ne i8 %x, 0) is false\n- This means the select returns false (the     │
│ false value)\n- However, cmp1 (icmp samesign eq i8 %x, -1) is poison when x │
│ = 0 because 0 and -1 don't have the same sign\n\nIn the target code:\n-     │
│ When x = 0, the function directly returns cmp1, which is poison\n\nThis     │
│ transforms a well-defined value (false) into poison, which violates LLVM's  │
│ poison semantics.\n\n2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:\n\nThe log shows that        │
│ InstCombine is calling `foldBooleanAndOr` through the `foldSelectOfBools`   │
│ function. The transformation happens at line 3368 in InstCombineSelect.cpp, │
│ where it replaces the select instruction with the result of                 │
│ `foldBooleanAndOr`.\n\nThe key issue is that `foldBooleanAndOr` is being    │
│ called with `IsLogical=true`, which should ensure poison safety, but the    │
│ function doesn't properly handle samesign icmp instructions.\n\n3. Root     │
│ Cause Analysis:\n\nLooking at the `impliesPoisonOrCond` function (lines     │
│ 3153-3181), it attempts to handle samesign icmp instructions, but there's a │
│ bug in the logic. The function checks if ValAssumedPoison is a samesign     │
│ icmp and V is a regular icmp with the same LHS operand.\n\nHowever, in our  │
│ case:\n- ValAssumedPoison is TrueVal (the samesign icmp: icmp samesign eq   │
│ i8 %x, -1)\n- V is CondVal (the regular icmp: icmp ne i8 %x, 0)\n- Expected │
│ is true (since we're in the FalseVal == Zero() branch)\n\nThe function      │
│ should return false because when x = 0:\n- The samesign icmp is poison\n-   │
│ The ne icmp is false\n- So we cannot replace \"select (ne x, 0), (samesign  │
│ eq x, -1), false\" with just \"(samesign eq x, -1)\"\n\nThe issue is that   │
│ `foldBooleanAndOr` is being called without proper poison safety checks for  │
│ samesign icmp instructions. The `impliesPoisonOrCond` check at line 3246    │
│ returns false (as we verified with the debugger), so it shouldn't be doing  │
│ the simple AND transformation. However, it's falling through to the         │
│ `foldBooleanAndOr` call at line 3366-3368.\n\nThe problem is that           │
│ `foldBooleanAndOr` doesn't know about the logical context and may perform   │
│ transformations that aren't poison-safe for samesign icmp                   │
│ instructions.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n\nThe fix is to add an         │
│ additional poison safety check before calling `foldBooleanAndOr` in the     │
│ logical context. Specifically, we need to ensure that when we have a        │
│ samesign icmp, we don't perform the transformation unless it's truly        │
│ safe.\n\nThe edit point is in                                               │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp at lines 3366-3368.   │
│ We need to add a check to ensure that if the TrueVal (or FalseVal) contains │
